                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tower</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-12-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 22, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Tower reports that the German Government announces officially the blockade
                    of Puerto Cabello and Maracaibo, to take effect December 20. Ships under other
                    flags than that of Venezuela sailing from West Indian or eastern American ports
                    before that date shall have an allowance of twenty days for sailing vessels and
                    ten days for steamships. Vessels coming from all other ports shall be allowed
                    forty days for sailing vessels and twenty days for steamers. Ships under other
                    flags than that of Venezuela and lying upon that date within the blockaded
                    harbors shall be allowed fifteen days. Ships which shall try to disregard the
                    blockade shall be subject to the rules applicable either by international law or
                    treaty provision to neutrals under such circumstances.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
